CRTP is a design pattern where a class passes itself as a template parameter to its base class. It enables static polymorphism, avoiding the performance cost of virtual functions. Syntax:
template <typename Derived>
class Base {
  // Methods
};
class Derived : public Base<Derived> {
  // Derived class
};

